cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about incorporating visual features into neural machine translation models. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper uses pre-trained convolutional neural networks to extract visual features. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses attention-based neural machine translation models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that could also apply as the paper involves developing models that can learn to translate between languages using visual features. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with incorporating visual features into a multi-modal translation model.
